{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ad13b13f-588b-4353-b34e-6998206cd15f","content":"Yes, you'll have **compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 drops support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n\n- **`net462`** — ❌ Not supported. MSTest v3 requires at least .NET Framework **4.7.2** (`net472`).\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — ❌ Not supported. MSTest v3 requires at least **.NET 6.0** (`net6.0`).\n- **`net5.0`** — ❌ Not supported. .NET 5 is out of support; MSTest v3 requires **net6.0+**.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update your target frameworks, e.g.:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net6.0;net472</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n\nThen update your package references to MSTest v3 (`3.x`) and the unified `MSTest` meta-package (which replaces the separate `TestFramework`/`TestAdapter` packages).\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2e033a76-342c-4a4b-9cd7-473222519b6a","outputTokens":255,"requestId":"A405:1FB426:14E04C0:1671EBF:6A02EC52"},"id":"cb93d14c-bcf9-4f47-92ef-d0f5b3c94e3f","timestamp":"2026-05-12T09:01:14.043Z","parentId":"cf66acff-bd3d-4de1-a795-e00d081f3fd3"}
